CROSS-MACHINE (S43 — the thing a thin boot drops; two machines, each a separate clone):
  AT BOOT, fetch+pull --rebase for scrml AND ../scrml-support (the storage hub) BEFORE reading state.
  scrml-support drifting behind origin = pa-scrml.md/PRIMER-refs/user-voice go STALE or MISSING -> a thinned boot.
  (This exact miss happened S240: scrml-support was 141 commits behind; pa-scrml.md read as absent.)
  AT WRAP, surface push-state for every repo touched; NEVER silent unpushed work.

CONCURRENT-SESSIONS (S242/S243 — the pre-wrap-next-session-start pattern; read-set step 0.5 is the boot half):
  >1 PA session live (cross-machine OR a successor booted BEFORE the predecessor wraps) => the
  `../scrml-support/handOffs/active-sessions/` board is the present-tense partition signal (the hand-off is a
  boot snapshot; the delta-log/digest are past-tense single-writer + collide cross-machine). Boot step 0.5 is
  UNCONDITIONAL: REGISTER your S<N>.md at boot even solo (a solo session that skips it is invisible to its own
  later successor — the S243 miss, which made the S244 pre-wrap boot false-alarm S243's live Realtime-P1 agent
  as "lost"), and READ the board before taking work. A LIVE sibling => SUCCESSOR-mode: full session on
  NON-intersecting write-footprints; sibling in-flight dispatches are CLAIMED not lost (no false alarms); only
  the WRAP defers (needs the predecessor's full hand-off + wrap signal). S-number minted at the serial wrap
  point. v2-hardened protocol: `active-sessions/README.md` (footprint claims + claims.md CAS via ff-only push +
  lease-until + pre-push self-revalidation). Durable home: a flobase `continuity`/`concurrent-sessions` module
  (README names it; proposal routed to flogence S244). This is the scrml reference flobase emulates until then.

PROJECT-INTENT: scrml is "the future of how programming is done for the browser" (Rule 2) — a WHOLE-STACK
  compiler: the developer writes markup+logic+style+data in one .scrml; the compiler owns routing, server/
  client split (INFERRED, §12), fetch, serialization, reactivity, SQL (?{}), realtime (<channel>), auth
  (session + @currentUser + protect=), deploy (scrml build --target fly|railway|render|docker). NOT a view
  layer over a BaaS — scrml IS the backend. V1 = language-1.0 (freeze on high coverage). The mitosis (many
  smaller compiler/language PAs + a near-autonomous conformance-driven compiler build) is the near horizon.

